.RS 2
Configures the port used by 
\fIerl_epmd\fR to listen for connection and connect to other nodes. If this flag is set, the Erlang VM will boot in distributed mode even if EPMD is not available. If not set, a port is chosen automatically (equivalent to port \fI0\fR). See \fIerl_epmd\fR for more details.
.PP
The now deprecated command line argument \fIerl_epmd_port <module>\fR has the same effect as the \fIerl_epmd_node_listen_port\fR configuration parameter. If this configuration parameter is defined, it will override the command line argument.


.RE

