.RS 2
Specifies default options for 
\fIlisten\fR (and \fIaccept\fR) sockets, see \fIinet\fR.

.RE

inet_dist_use_interface = ip_address()
.RS 2
If the host of an Erlang node has many network interfaces, this parameter specifies which one to listen on. For the type definition of 
\fIip_address()\fR, see \fIinet\fR.

.RE


.sp
.RS 4
.ie n \{\
\h'-04'\(bu\h'+03'\c
.\}
.el \{\
